   "author_association" : "CONTRIBUTOR",
   "body" : "This has the benefit of moving this StartShutdown call out of the blockstorage file and thus out of the kernel's responsibility. The user can now decide if he wants to start shutdown / interrupt after a block import or not.\r\n\r\nOnce https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/27607 is merged (splitting up the block import and `LoadMempool` steps), the `return_after_import` bool can be removed.\r\n\r\nThis also simplifies https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/28048, making it one fewer shutdown call to handle.",
